        <div id="e14" style="position:absolute;left:1;top:0;width:125;height:124;"><img src="images/site_logo_-_125x125_-_transparent.gif" width="125" height="124" alt=""></div>        <div id="e15" style="position:absolute;left:7;top:551;width:998;height:44;"><img src="images/generic_dusk_footer.gif" width="998" height="44" alt=""></div>        <div id="e16" style="position:absolute;left:345;top:564;width:308;height:18;"><span class="text"><font color="#D4A84B" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Copyright &#169; Dominion Shotokan Karate Club, LLC 2010<br/></span></font></span>        </div>
        <div id="e17" style="position:absolute;left:155;top:175;width:675;height:300;"><span class="text"><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">These are rules and regulations for the Dominion Shotokan Karate Club, LLC (DSKC). They have been designed to help <br/>students feel more comfortable from the beginning and instill a basic knowledge of the culture, terminology and procedures <br/>that are required in a </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">dojo</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">. It will require some time and effort during your training to learn the proper procedures, rules of <br/>etiquette and aspects of Japanese culture. This is understood as practicing karate is much different than most endeavors <br/>you have undertaken in your life thus far. You will make mistakes; learn from them. If you have questions, feel free to ask the <br/></span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sensei </span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">or a </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sempai </span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">at the proper time. We are all here to help you in your journey.<br><br>We practice the Japanese art of Shotokan Karate and are affiliated with the International Shotokan Karate Federation (ISKF) <br/>headquartered in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. The chairman and chief instructor is Master Teruyuki Okazaki, 10th Dan and a <br/>direct student of the founder of Shotokan, Master Gichin Funakoshi. All students are required to become members of the <br/>ISKF and can participate in all ISKF tournaments, special trainings, Master Camps and Fall Camps. In addition, students <br/>who are traveling should be able to practice at any ISKF</span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> dojo</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">, worldwide, for a nominal fee. You will need to see your <br/>instructor prior to your trip to obtain a letter of introduction for the </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sensei</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> at the other </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">dojo</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">, to discuss the small gift, </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">omiyage</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">, <br/>you should bring to the </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">sensei</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;"> and about your expected conduct. Remember, you are representing our </span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">dojo</span></font></i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">; follow all their <br/>rules and do your best during your training visit.<br><br></span></font><i><font color="#979BA0" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">&#8220;The ultimate aim of karate-do lies not in victory or defeat, but in the perfection of character of the person who studies it.&#8221;<br>Master Gichin Funakoshi<br/></span></font></i></span>        </div>
        <div id="e18" style="position:absolute;left:850;top:175;width:100;height:200;"><span class="text"><b><font color="#D4A84B" size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">Dojo Rules <br/>Navigation<br><br></span></font></b><a href="DojoRules-Introduction.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">01 </span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-Introduction.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">I</span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-Introduction.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">ntroduction<br></span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-FAQs.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">02 FAQs<br></span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-Etiquette.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">03 Etiquette<br></span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-Protocols.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">04 Protocols<br></span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-Ranks.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">05 Ranks<br></span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-Events.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">06 Events<br></span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-Terminology.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">07 Terminology<br></span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-ShotokanKata.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">08 Kata<br></span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-DojoKun.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">09 Dojo Kun<br></span></font></a><a href="DojoRules-NijuKun.html"><font size="2"><span style="font-size:12px;line-height:15px;">10 Niju Kun<br/></span></font></a></span>        </div>
